%N A395673 The first (2*n-1)-digit palindromic prime occurring in the decimal expansion of Pi.
%H A395673 GitHub, <a href="https://github.com/fontes-mrc/pi-palindromes">Pi Prime Palindromes Challenge</a>.
%e A395673 a(1) = 3, because the first 2*1-1 = 1 digit of the decimal expansion of Pi is a palindromic prime.
%e A395673 a(2) = 383, because the first palindrome with 2*2-1 = 3 digits occurring in the decimal expansion of Pi = 3.141592653589793238462643383... that is prime is 383.
